We subdivided the protein sequence positions into Neutral and Toggle types on the basis of their variant labels. We previously defined Toggles (37) as positions intolerant of any change, while Neutrals are defined here as positions that can tolerate almost all substitutions without functional changes. Each sequence position x was classified (Equation 2) as Toggle or Neutral. If all but at most one variant at x were neutral, we labeled x Neutral (N; 153 positions). If all but at most two variants were severe, we labeled x a Toggle (T; 66 positions). If none of these two conditions held true, x was deemed unknown (374 positions; Unknown set).(2)\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
