Performance for both ntModel and funtrpModel was reported as accuracy, precision, recall, and F-measure (F1 score, Equation 3). For each position type (N, R or T) at every score cutoff, true positives (TP) were the correctly predicted position types. For each type (e.g. N), false positives (FP) were the positions incorrectly predicted to be of that type (e.g. R or T positions, predicted as N), while false negatives (FN) were that type positions incorrectly predicted as something else (e.g. N positions, predicted as R or T).(3)\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
